org.vu.contest

Interface ContestSubmission


  • public interface ContestSubmission

    This interface must be implemented by any class to be submitted to the contest. It specifies the generic structure a player's algorithm must have so it can be run by the contest run system.

    An object of a class implementing this interface is instantiated by the contest run system. Method setSeed is called to provide a random seed, then method setEvaluation passes an object implementing the ContestEvaluation interface and, finally, method run is called to run the algorithm.

    The evaluation object passed with method setEvaluation is used in the implementation of the method run to get problem information and data and evaluate algorithm results. See the description of interface ContestEvaluation.

    • Method Detail

      • setEvaluation

        void setEvaluation(ContestEvaluation eval)
        This method passes the evaluation object that is used by the algorithm to test its results and register its performance with the contest system. The sumbission class implementing this interface must call the evaluation object's methods to get data and properties relevant to the evaluation problem and test results (see ContestEvaluation).
        Parameters:
        eval - The object this algorithm will use for evaluation.

      • setSeed

        void setSeed(long seed)
        This method must be used to set the seed of any random process of the implementing class.
        Parameters:
        seed - The random seed.

      • run

        void run()
        This method is called by the contest run system to run the implementing class. No return value is required, the evaluation object will keep track of tested results and corresponding performances and will provide the contest run system with overall performance metrics after the run is over.
